  _id: joren
  _characterName: Joren
  _role: Smith / tool upgrades
  _age: Forties
  _home: Joren's forge
  _work: Blacksmithing, tools, and repair hardware
  _keepsake: Smith's hammer
  _tagline: The smith who respects a clean edge, honest payment, and useful work.
  _leadParagraph: Joren is broad as a doorframe, with soot-black forearms, a leather
    apron, and pride he usually disguises as irritation.
  _backgroundParagraph: He forges Wren a proper horn-handled knife and supplies the
    hinges needed when Hollowfen's boarded cottages begin to open again.
  _perspectiveParagraph: Joren judges people by whether they know what a tool is
    for. Pretty costs extra, cuts worse, and earns very little patience at his anvil.
  _kitItems: []
  _heroPortrait: {fileID: 0}
  _pullquote: Pretty costs extra and cuts worse.
